The paper deals with regular languages and their complexity measures, which are topics related to formal languages (cs.FL) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of semigroups and automata also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the study of complexity measures is often relevant to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
